<subSubSection id="C30FB2903522FFEEFF17FAA8FE24F968" pageId="1" pageNumber="357" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BAAE11B3522FFEEFF17FAA8FE24F968" blockId="1.[151,1437,1370,1684]" pageId="1" pageNumber="357">
<emphasis id="B9613D093522FFEEFF17FAA8FF77FA88" bold="true" box="[151,216,1370,1396]" pageId="1" pageNumber="357">Note:</emphasis>
New genera could be created for 
<taxonomicName id="4C159A983522FFEEFDD2FAA9FD72FA88" authority="Muñoz-Charry &amp; Galvis &amp; Martínez, 2022" authorityName="Muñoz-Charry &amp; Galvis &amp; Martínez" authorityYear="2022" box="[594,733,1370,1396]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Lapsias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quimbaya" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9613D093522FFEEFDD2FAA9FD72FA88" box="[594,733,1370,1396]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="357">L. quimbaya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9613D093522FFEEFD64FAA8FC91FA88" bold="true" box="[740,830,1370,1396]" pageId="1" pageNumber="357">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25280723522FFEEFD64FAA8FC91FA88" box="[740,830,1370,1396]" pageId="1" pageNumber="357" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C159A983522FFEEFCCCFAA9FC10FA88" authority="Muñoz-Charry &amp; Galvis &amp; Martínez, 2022" authorityName="Muñoz-Charry &amp; Galvis &amp; Martínez" authorityYear="2022" box="[844,959,1371,1396]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Lapsias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tayrona" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9613D093522FFEEFCCCFAA9FC10FA88" box="[844,959,1371,1396]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="357">L. tayrona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9613D093522FFEEFC46FAA8FBB0FA88" bold="true" box="[966,1055,1370,1396]" pageId="1" pageNumber="357">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25280723522FFEEFC46FAA8FBB0FA88" box="[966,1055,1370,1396]" pageId="1" pageNumber="357" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C159A983522FFEEFBD5FAA9FA33FA88" authority="Maddison, 2012" authorityName="Maddison" authorityYear="2012" box="[1109,1436,1370,1396]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Lapsias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="canandea">
<emphasis id="B9613D093522FFEEFBD5FAA9FB4FFA88" box="[1109,1248,1370,1396]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="357">L. canandea</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF849CEA3522FFEEFB66FAA8FA33FA88" author="Maddison, W. P." box="[1254,1436,1370,1396]" pageId="1" pageNumber="357" pagination="51 - 65" refId="ref8664" refString="Maddison, W. P. (2012) Five new species of lapsiine jumping spiders from Ecuador (Araneae: Salticidae). Zootaxa, 3424 (1), 51 - 65. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3424.1.3" type="journal article" year="2012">Maddison, 2012</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
given that their palp conformation is very distinctive from the 
<typeStatus id="54AE5FB93522FFEEFCC8FA8CFCD7FA64" box="[840,888,1406,1432]" pageId="1" pageNumber="357">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<emphasis id="B9613D093522FFEEFC73FA8DFBFEFA64" box="[1011,1105,1407,1432]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="357">
<taxonomicName id="4C159A983522FFEEFC73FA8DFBE2FA64" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1900" box="[1011,1101,1407,1432]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Lapsias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Lapsias</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C159A983522FFEEFBD7FA8DFA37FA64" authority="Simon, 1900" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1900" box="[1111,1432,1406,1432]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Lapsias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="estebanensis">
<emphasis id="B9613D093522FFEEFBD7FA8DFAAEFA64" box="[1111,1281,1406,1432]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="357">L. estebanensis</emphasis>
Simon, 1900
</taxonomicName>
, and its close relatives 
<taxonomicName id="4C159A983522FFEEFE0BFA51FD0EFA40" authority="Maddison, 2012" authorityName="Maddison" authorityYear="2012" box="[395,673,1442,1468]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Lapsias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lorax">
<emphasis id="B9613D093522FFEEFE0BFA51FE4DFA40" box="[395,482,1442,1468]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="357">L. lorax</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF849CEA3522FFEEFE69FA50FD0EFA40" author="Maddison, W. P." box="[489,673,1442,1468]" pageId="1" pageNumber="357" pagination="51 - 65" refId="ref8664" refString="Maddison, W. P. (2012) Five new species of lapsiine jumping spiders from Ecuador (Araneae: Salticidae). Zootaxa, 3424 (1), 51 - 65. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3424.1.3" type="journal article" year="2012">Maddison, 2012</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C159A983522FFEEFD2BFA51FC7FFA40" authority="Simon, 1901" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1901" box="[683,976,1442,1468]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Lapsias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tovarensis">
<emphasis id="B9613D093522FFEEFD2BFA51FC96FA40" box="[683,825,1443,1468]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="357">L. tovarensis</emphasis>
Simon, 1901
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C159A983522FFEEFC5BFA51FB56FA40" authority="Simon, 1900" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1900" box="[987,1273,1442,1468]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Lapsias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cyrboides">
<emphasis id="B9613D093522FFEEFC5BFA51FBCBFA40" box="[987,1124,1442,1468]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="357">L. cyrboides</emphasis>
Simon, 1900
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C159A983522FFEEFAADFA51FE83FA1C" authority="Simon, 1900" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1900" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Lapsias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ciliatus">
<emphasis id="B9613D093522FFEEFAADFA51FA33FA40" box="[1325,1436,1442,1468]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="357">L. ciliatus</emphasis>
Simon, 1900
</taxonomicName>
. However, this differentiation is not clear in females, and epigynes of 
<emphasis id="B9613D093522FFEEFBD6FA35FA98FA1C" box="[1110,1335,1478,1504]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="357">
<taxonomicName id="4C159A983522FFEEFBD6FA35FB1BFA1C" authorityName="Maddison" authorityYear="2012" box="[1110,1204,1478,1504]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Lapsias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lorax">L. lorax</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C159A983522FFEEFB41FA35FA98FA1C" authority="Muñoz-Charry &amp; Galvis &amp; Martínez, 2022" authorityName="Muñoz-Charry &amp; Galvis &amp; Martínez" authorityYear="2022" box="[1217,1335,1479,1504]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Lapsias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tayrona" status="sp. nov.">L. tayrona</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B9613D093522FFEEFAC1FA34FA33FA1C" bold="true" box="[1345,1436,1478,1504]" pageId="1" pageNumber="357">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25280723522FFEEFAC1FA34FA33FA1C" box="[1345,1436,1478,1504]" pageId="1" pageNumber="357" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C159A983522FFEEFF46FA19FDADF9F8" authority="Maddison, 2012" authorityName="Maddison" authorityYear="2012" box="[198,514,1514,1540]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Lapsias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guamani">
<emphasis id="B9613D093522FFEEFF46FA19FEEAF9F8" box="[198,325,1515,1540]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="357">L. guamani</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF849CEA3522FFEEFECCFA18FDADF9F8" author="Maddison, W. P." box="[332,514,1514,1540]" pageId="1" pageNumber="357" pagination="51 - 65" refId="ref8664" refString="Maddison, W. P. (2012) Five new species of lapsiine jumping spiders from Ecuador (Araneae: Salticidae). Zootaxa, 3424 (1), 51 - 65. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3424.1.3" type="journal article" year="2012">Maddison, 2012</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
are all similar. On the other hand, males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C159A983522FFEEFC69FA19FB3FF9F8" authority="Muñoz-Charry &amp; Galvis &amp; Martínez, 2022" authorityName="Muñoz-Charry &amp; Galvis &amp; Martínez" authorityYear="2022" box="[1001,1168,1514,1540]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Lapsias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tequendama" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9613D093522FFEEFC69FA19FB3FF9F8" box="[1001,1168,1514,1540]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="357">L. tequendama</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9613D093522FFEEFB16FA18FB40F9F8" bold="true" box="[1174,1263,1514,1540]" pageId="1" pageNumber="357">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25280723522FFEEFB16FA18FB40F9F8" box="[1174,1263,1514,1540]" pageId="1" pageNumber="357" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C159A983522FFEEFB7DFA19FADBF9F8" authority="Muñoz-Charry &amp; Galvis &amp; Martínez, 2022" authorityName="Muñoz-Charry &amp; Galvis &amp; Martínez" authorityYear="2022" box="[1277,1396,1515,1540]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Lapsias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iguaque" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9613D093522FFEEFB7DFA19FADBF9F8" box="[1277,1396,1515,1540]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="357">L. iguaque</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9613D093522FFEEFAFBFA18FF67F9D4" bold="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="357">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25280723522FFEEFAFBFA18FF67F9D4" pageId="1" pageNumber="357" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C159A983522FFEEFE81F9FDFE28F9D4" authority="Muñoz-Charry &amp; Galvis &amp; Martínez, 2022" authorityName="Muñoz-Charry &amp; Galvis &amp; Martínez" authorityYear="2022" box="[257,391,1550,1576]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Lapsias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="walekeru" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9613D093522FFEEFE81F9FDFE28F9D4" box="[257,391,1550,1576]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="357">L. walekeru</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9613D093522FFEEFE0FF9FCFE46F9D4" bold="true" box="[399,489,1550,1576]" pageId="1" pageNumber="357">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25280723522FFEEFE0FF9FCFE46F9D4" box="[399,489,1550,1576]" pageId="1" pageNumber="357" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
seem to be more related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C159A983522FFEEFCA8F9FDFC1CF9D4" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1900" box="[808,947,1550,1576]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Lapsias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cyrboides">
<emphasis id="B9613D093522FFEEFCA8F9FDFC1CF9D4" box="[808,947,1550,1576]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="357">L. cyrboides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C159A983522FFEEFC6CF9FDFBF2F9D4" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1900" box="[1004,1117,1550,1576]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Lapsias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ciliatus">
<emphasis id="B9613D093522FFEEFC6CF9FDFBF2F9D4" box="[1004,1117,1550,1576]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="357">L. ciliatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because they share a robust embolus that arises prolateraly and distally at the bulb. Based on that, it may be prudent to include the five new species described herein in 
<taxonomicName id="4C159A983522FFEEFE4FF9A5FD89F98C" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1900" box="[463,550,1623,1648]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Lapsias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9613D093522FFEEFE4FF9A5FD89F98C" box="[463,550,1623,1648]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="357">Lapsias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to avoid creating uncertainty in the tribe until their phylogenetic relationships are better understood.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
